1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:42,390 --> 00:00:48,850
[1st March, announcement of
scholarship name list]

3
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:04,269
Mark, let's look forward
to the result together.

4
00:01:06,420 --> 00:01:07,990
No matter what the result is,

5
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:11,590
I will make sure you won't let go of me.

6
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:12,930
Understood?

7
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:47,229
The bow and the wind?

8
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:48,759
Do you know

9
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,880
what the wind means to the bow?

10
00:01:51,420 --> 00:01:53,910
Without the wind to carry the arrows,

11
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,979
the arrows might head
towards the wrong direction.

12
00:01:56,729 --> 00:01:58,550
Now, I belong to you.

13
00:02:05,290 --> 00:02:05,980
It's...

14
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,140
You see,

15
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:15,510
can I spend the night
in your room tonight?

16
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,890
What did you say?

17
00:02:24,579 --> 00:02:25,329
So,

18
00:02:27,170 --> 00:02:29,150
can I spend the night
in your room tonight?

19
00:02:32,579 --> 00:02:34,410
The bed light in my room keeps flickering.

20
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:36,800
I heard the lizards as well.

21
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,829
They're very loud. I'm scared.

22
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:47,770
Of course.

23
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,800
You can spend the night
in my room tonight.

24
00:02:53,850 --> 00:02:54,770
Thank you.

25
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:56,720
Come in then.

26
00:03:12,830 --> 00:03:16,680
You can sleep on the bed.
I'll sleep on the sofa.

27
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:19,250
Thank you.

28
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,570
Do you need anything, Wayu?

29
00:03:42,410 --> 00:03:43,150
I'm fine.

30
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,960
Are you cold, Wayu?

31
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:40,930
You can use the blanket then.
Don't worry about me.

32
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:43,420
Aren't you cold?

33
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:46,440
It's fine. I can stand the cold.

34
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:51,470
Do you wish to sleep on the same bed?

35
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:55,950
Come, P'Thanu.

36
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,270
If we want to stand the cold together,

37
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,450
we should share the warmth together too.

38
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:07,720
-Okay then.
-Come.

39
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:46,620
I don't stay still when I sleep.

40
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:49,460
I'm afraid I might interrupt your sleep.

41
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:53,380
Let me use the pillow as a barrier.

42
00:06:57,780 --> 00:06:58,880
I don't stay still when I sleep too.

43
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,710
I wonder if this tiny pillow

44
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,600
can hold me off?

45
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,120
Good night.

46
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:19,100
Good night, P'Thanu.

47
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,050
[Hello, P'Kit?]

48
00:07:50,730 --> 00:07:53,960
[Sorry about that.
I just finished my project.]

49
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,659
It's fine. I can wait for you.

50
00:07:57,890 --> 00:07:59,000
Have you finished your homework?

51
00:07:59,409 --> 00:08:00,640
I have.

52
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,700
[The other faculties were already done
with their mid-semester exams,]

53
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:06,470
yet, the Faculty of Engineering spent
an entire year to complete their project.

54
00:08:07,190 --> 00:08:09,350
The Faculty of Medicine has
a never-ending supply of exams as well.

55
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,560
I always see you with a book.

56
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:18,410
Mark,

57
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,060
there's one more week before
the result will be announced.

58
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:24,790
I remember that.

59
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,930
I cross out the date
day by day with a pen.

60
00:08:26,930 --> 00:08:29,230
I've already used up two pens
by just doing so.

61
00:08:30,340 --> 00:08:32,530
[You exaggerate everything
just like usual.]

62
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,890
Besides exaggerating facts,

63
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:39,200
I'm very loyal in love as well.

64
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:42,500
Yeah, Mark. You're the best.

65
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,790
Should we view

66
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,330
the result together
on the day of its announcement?

67
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:48,780
Okay.

68
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:52,230
No matter what the result is,

69
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:55,570
at least we'll be together on that day.

70
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:58,190
That's right, P'Kit.

71
00:09:06,830 --> 00:09:08,660
[P'Kit, you should go to sleep now.]

72
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:09,930
It's very late.

73
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:12,910
Yeah, I feel sleepy too.

74
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:15,360
Good night, P'Kit.

75
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:17,750
Good night.

76
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:18,600
[Wait, P'Kit.]

77
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:20,340
What's wrong?

78
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:26,410
Can you keep the camera on tonight?

79
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:35,000
Fine. But you aren't allowed to
let your imagination run wild.

80
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:36,780
Oh, P'Kit.

81
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:39,530
What kind of person do you think I am?

82
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:40,950
You're that type of person.

83
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,910
[P'Kit, what are you wearing?]

84
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:16,660
Where did you place your hand?

85
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,020
Mark, be serious.

86
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:19,870
Who did you chat with on the phone

87
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:21,410
when I wasn't around?

88
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:23,520
[Hey, P'Kit,]

89
00:10:23,850 --> 00:10:24,800
[I was just joking.]

90
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,390
[Are you jealous?]

91
00:10:32,130 --> 00:10:34,540
Let's stop chatting. I need to sleep now.

92
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:36,450
Good night, P'Kit.

93
00:10:41,090 --> 00:10:43,480
P'Kit, don't sleep
with your back facing me.

94
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,960
Turn over.

95
00:10:45,930 --> 00:10:46,780
[P'Kit!]

96
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:18,860
How could I sleep

97
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,700
when you're doing this?

98
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:06,120
Hello, Mark?

99
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:08,040
What's the matter?

100
00:14:08,330 --> 00:14:09,280
[Hey.]

101
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:11,740
[You rarely contacted me]

102
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:14,190
[after you went on a trip with P'Thanu.]

103
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:16,280
Why did you call me
this early in the morning?

104
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:20,420
[I was worried about you.
I didn't see you for some time.]

105
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:23,340
I'm isolating myself from the world
as I'm on a relaxing trip.

106
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,500
[Fine, you can isolate
yourself from the world.]

107
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:29,660
[But you shouldn't isolate yourself
from your friends too.]

108
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:34,220
[By the way, I dreamt of you last night.]

109
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,490
[I dreamt that you were
pestered by a snake.]

110
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:43,110
Is that so? That's a strange dream.

111
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:47,050
[By the way, is P'Thanu awake yet?]

112
00:14:48,390 --> 00:14:49,560
How should I know?

113
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,730
He's in his own room.

114
00:14:52,770 --> 00:14:55,750
[Oh, are you guys
sleeping in different rooms?]

115
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,790
Let's cut it short. I'm still sleepy.

116
00:14:58,790 --> 00:14:59,870
I need to continue my sleep.

117
00:15:04,130 --> 00:15:06,700
[Wait, whose sound was that?]

118
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,290
What sound? There's no sound.

119
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,190
Why would there be a sound here?

120
00:15:13,950 --> 00:15:16,250
I'll hang up now. Goodbye.

121
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:17,350
[Wait, Wayu!]

122
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,390
He actually dreamt of that?

123
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,500
But the difference is

124
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:33,010
that a person is beside me
instead of a snake.

125
00:15:51,180 --> 00:15:52,040
P'Thanu.

126
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:56,230
Are you sure you slept alone last night?

127
00:15:59,130 --> 00:16:04,350
If so, who was the person
sleeping beside me last night?

128
00:16:08,180 --> 00:16:10,830
Do you want me to tell him that
I was sleeping beside you then?

129
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,220
The entire school will know about it
in a matter of seconds.

130
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,090
Didn't you say you were sleepy?

131
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,750
I don't want to wake up yet.

132
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:23,640
Come, let's continue our sleep.

133
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:16,450
You're such a lazy bum. Time to wake up.

134
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,250
You'll get a headache
if you sleep too much.

135
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,990
Go and take a shower.

136
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:33,700
If you're not willing to wake up,

137
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,420
I'll carry you to the bathroom
and take a shower with you.

138
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:32,060
Let's go.

139
00:18:54,150 --> 00:18:56,460
My salmon rice bowl is finally here.

140
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,890
Mine was here long ago.

141
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:11,590
[It's like we're having a meal
at the same restaurant.]

142
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,960
It's been a long time since
we visited that restaurant.

143
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:21,040
It was the restaurant
where I first kissed you on the cheek.

144
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:22,740
[Hey.]

145
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:24,730
[You do remember
those incidents clearly, huh?]

146
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:30,150
We'll be in different time zones
when you go to the US in the future.

147
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:33,350
We might not be able to
have our meals together like this.

148
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:40,110
Yeah.

149
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:45,580
But as long as I know that
you're having your meals on time

150
00:19:45,790 --> 00:19:48,330
and enough sleep, I'll be happy.

151
00:19:48,330 --> 00:19:50,540
If you're leading a happy
and satisfying life over there,

152
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:53,060
I'll be satisfied.

153
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:00,270
Me too, Mark.

154
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:07,510
Come, let me feed you.

155
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,380
Let's do it.

156
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:18,490
Ah.

157
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:23,870
[Oh.]

158
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,200
[Just you wait.]

159
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:27,700
[You want to tease me like this?]

160
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,490
P'Kit.

161
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:35,920
Come, let's dig in.

162
00:20:43,230 --> 00:20:44,670
Did you have fun?

163
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:45,530
I did.

164
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,190
Let's go on another trip in the future.

165
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,140
Sure.

166
00:20:49,870 --> 00:20:53,360
Thank you for bringing me on a trip.

167
00:20:53,570 --> 00:20:55,040
It was relaxing.

168
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:57,250
I want to thank you too.

169
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,150
Thank you for joining me on my trip.

170
00:21:01,410 --> 00:21:02,570
I've been looking forward to
our Chiangmai trip

171
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:04,190
since today.

172
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:07,890
Did you pick up Mark's bad habit from him?

173
00:21:08,790 --> 00:21:10,590
I'll return first.

174
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,400
I'll fetch you to class tomorrow.

175
00:21:26,930 --> 00:21:29,820
I'll head inside first. Goodbye.

176
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:08,640
Focus on the class, okay?

177
00:22:09,610 --> 00:22:10,440
Okay.

178
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,720
I'll pick you up in the evening.

179
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:16,170
Okay.

180
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,220
Thank you for sending me to my class.

181
00:22:24,010 --> 00:22:24,470
See you.

182
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,850
Hello.

183
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:05,720
Hello, N'Wayu.

184
00:23:05,970 --> 00:23:09,110
Are you having lunch alone today?

185
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:12,490
What's the matter? Why are you smiling?

186
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:14,610
Hey.

187
00:23:14,740 --> 00:23:17,890
Everyone in the school
is talking about it.

188
00:23:18,070 --> 00:23:22,780
Your relationship with P'Thanu
is so sweet

189
00:23:22,780 --> 00:23:25,500
that you've attracted
a nest of ants to the school.

190
00:23:26,060 --> 00:23:27,000
You're exaggerating it.

191
00:23:28,730 --> 00:23:30,710
Hey, which progress have you guys reached?

192
00:23:30,710 --> 00:23:32,880
Why didn't you tell
your good friend, Mark, about it?

193
00:23:33,230 --> 00:23:34,970
It's progressing naturally.
There's nothing special about it.

194
00:23:34,970 --> 00:23:36,470
Oh.

195
00:23:36,470 --> 00:23:39,230
Don't lie to me. I know what happened.

196
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:42,740
You two slept in the same room
during your trip.

197
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,360
Mark, lower your voice!

198
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:46,990
Did something else happen?

199
00:23:46,990 --> 00:23:47,820
Don't act like that.

200
00:23:50,650 --> 00:23:51,170
Mark.

201
00:23:51,580 --> 00:23:52,370
Hello.

202
00:23:52,610 --> 00:23:53,130
Here you go.

203
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:57,500
My goodness!

204
00:23:58,290 --> 00:24:01,290
P'Thanu, how did you know

205
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:05,080
that rice with stir-fried pork and
minced garlic is my favourite?

206
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:07,910
Mark, P'Thanu bought it for me.

207
00:24:09,020 --> 00:24:10,470
Thank you, P'Thanu.

208
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:17,020
My blood sugar level has gone
through the roof because of you, friend.

209
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:20,640
I think I should leave first.
I'm so envious and jealous of you.

210
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:24,430
And, I'm afraid
I'll get diabetes from this.

211
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:26,310
I'll hit you with my spoon.

212
00:24:26,310 --> 00:24:28,460
I'll make a move now. Goodbye.

213
00:24:31,850 --> 00:24:33,410
He was so funny.

214
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:34,920
Let's dig in.

215
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:42,520
Have you stretched your legs?

216
00:24:43,750 --> 00:24:52,540
[Pok: I wish to apologise to you.]
[Pok: ......]

217
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:59,470
[Pok: I will train hard and be selected
for the national swimming competition.]

218
00:24:59,470 --> 00:25:02,450
[Read]

219
00:25:05,490 --> 00:25:07,760
Pok, come and get ready.

220
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:09,490
-Coming, Coach.
-Hurry up.

221
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,020
Stop skiving! Hurry up!

222
00:25:12,890 --> 00:25:13,580
Hurry!

223
00:25:13,580 --> 00:25:14,280
Hurry!

224
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:18,930
Be serious!

225
00:25:21,610 --> 00:25:24,600
Over here, it's like this.

226
00:25:25,950 --> 00:25:27,300
Everyone, we're here.

227
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:28,490
Have you guys been
waiting for a long time?

228
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:29,720
We're here.

229
00:25:30,340 --> 00:25:31,640
Replenish your energy with these.

230
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:33,950
Thank you.

231
00:25:36,820 --> 00:25:37,760
Thank you, P'Wayu.

232
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:38,680
Thank you for tutoring us.

233
00:25:41,190 --> 00:25:41,670
Do you guys know something?

234
00:25:41,670 --> 00:25:44,000
Next week, they'll be holding
the "Cold Moon Warm Star" event.

235
00:25:44,470 --> 00:25:45,730
It's the school's annual music festival,

236
00:25:45,730 --> 00:25:46,170
right?

237
00:25:46,170 --> 00:25:47,650
Yeah, that's right.

238
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:48,770
Let me say this first.

239
00:25:48,770 --> 00:25:50,110
I won't miss out on this event
no matter what.

240
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:51,590
Last year,

241
00:25:51,810 --> 00:25:54,290
P'Mark and P'Wayu sang on stage.

242
00:25:54,740 --> 00:25:55,370
Is that so?

243
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:57,340
That's right.

244
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:59,200
P'Mark dedicated a song to P'Kit,

245
00:25:59,780 --> 00:26:01,540
and P'Wayu dedicated a song to P'Thanu.

246
00:26:01,540 --> 00:26:02,270
They were so sweet!

247
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:03,790
Yeah, right?

248
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:05,390
Sab.

249
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:07,620
Will you sing on stage this year?

250
00:26:07,870 --> 00:26:10,830
I think it'll be 100 times sweeter
than last year's performance.

251
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:12,480
Yeah.

252
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:14,220
Please sing on stage this year, P'Wayu.

253
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,860
Let everyone there experience

254
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:17,980
the warmness of love once again.

255
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:18,980
He's right.

256
00:26:20,130 --> 00:26:21,660
That's a great idea, P'Wayu.

257
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:24,800
Let's make this a surprise.

258
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,190
P'Thanu should only know
about this at the very last second.

259
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:30,230
A surprise?

260
00:26:30,550 --> 00:26:31,780
What kind of surprise?

261
00:26:37,150 --> 00:26:38,660
You heard wrongly, P'Thanu.

262
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:41,820
We were talking about lemongrass.

263
00:26:41,820 --> 00:26:43,880
We want to get rid of the mosquitoes
by using lemongrass,

264
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:44,940
am I right?

265
00:26:44,940 --> 00:26:46,400
That's right.

266
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,420
We'll get rid of the mosquitoes
by using lemongrass.

267
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,130
Let's go, P'Thanu.

268
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:52,900
We'll be stuck in the traffic
